messages.speech:
The Medicare Benefits Schedule or MBS, in short, is a list of health professional services subsidised by the Australian Government. An item number from MBS is the specific medical service you will receive or have received from a doctor or medical centre. The amount of money you will have to spend and or will be able to claim depends on this number.
e.g. Common GP item numbers are:  23, 36, 44, 5040
